resource.name: St. Petersburg Police Department Calls for Service Activity Map
resource.description: Data contained in this data set has been extracted from the St. Petersburg Police Department's Computer-Aided Dispatch (CAD) system. In accordance with Florida State Statute 119.071, victim information (i.e. addresses) associated with incidents of Sexual Battery, Sexual Offenses, Child Abuse, and Adult Abuse are considered confidential and are exempt from public release. In addition, events classified as forensic services, off duty, alarms and administrative in nature are excluded. Calls for service events do not typically represent the final of state of a police investigation. Specifically, the calls for service event disposition, classification and location can change throughout the course of an initial on scene investigation and should not be relied on for official crime reporting initiatives. This data, by its nature, is at best, a snapshot of police activity at a particular location and time and can prove useful for establishing the volume of complaints and police-initiated activity throughout the City of St. Petersburg, neighborhoods and political districts.  Ultimately, calls for service events should not be confused with official City of St. Petersburg Uniform Crime Reporting (UCR) reports, which are made available on a semi-annual and annual basis from the Florida Department of Law Enforcement (FDLE).

resource.name: Water Resources Preventive and Corrective Work Orders
resource.description:
The following data displays all of the preventive and corrective work orders at the Water Resource Department. The provided data is from 10/01/2018 to Current Date and is updated on a daily basis. The date column is based on the actual finished date of each of the work order task and its only showing finished work order tasks. The divisions are classified based on the crews assigned to respective division as for special projects such as customer funded the department field in empty in Work and Asset Management (WAM) system. 

The data set can be filtered down to each individual division to measure their respective preventive vs corrective work performed as classified in the Work Type columns. As each division reports preventive and corrective work differently the type is classified differently for all divisions. WRF/WTD classifies the work based on the type field, WSM classifies it based on work class category and WWM is based on failure codes.

The Budget column represents the burden or overhead charges associated with that task and costs have to be posted in WAM in order for it to have any values. Labor hours are the approved time sheets that are entered in WAM.
